<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="264" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,547,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[855,886,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">bi-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[941,1039,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">digitatus</emphasis>
, referring to the two thumb-shaped processes of the transtilla in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
